        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 2:08PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 207 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Capulin, or 15 miles southwest of San Luis Valley Airport, moving
east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Manassa, Sanford, La Jara, Romeo, Capulin, and Bountiful.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
